This is a survey of the postage stamps and postal history of ``Guinea''.



The Republic of Guinea (Fr: R\'epublique de Guin\'ee ) is a country in West Africa formerly known as French Guinea. Conakry is the capital, the seat of the national government, and the largest city. \footnote{This is the first footnote.}

